io.github.utk003.json.traditional.node

Interface JSONStorageElement<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The key/index type for this JSONStorageElement
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JSONArray, JSONObject

    public interface JSONStorageElement<E>
    An interface that represents the two JSON element types that can hold other elements as children in a JSON tree: objects and arrays.

    Arrays can be differentiated from objects based on the type of the parameter: JSON arrays will use Integers as their index, and JSON objects will use Strings.

    Of the default implementations for JSONValue node provided, only JSONArray and JSONObject, which correspond to JSON arrays and JSON objects respectively, implement JSONStorageElement.

    Version:
    February 23, 2021
    Author:
    Utkarsh Priyam (utk003)

      • getElementsPaired

        ImmutablePair<LinkedList<String>,LinkedList<JSONValue>> getElementsPaired()
        Returns an ImmutablePair of LinkedLists that hold all of this JSONStorageElement's JSONValue children as well as their corresponding keys/indices.

        This method is particularly useful in transforming a JSON tree back into a Scanner in a single pass. Check out OOJTranslator.JSONValueStreamer for more details.

        Returns:
        This JSONStorageElement's children and their keys/indices as a pair of LinkedLists
